text.section:
The State Advisory Board consists of the following 19 members appointed by the Governor:
one representative of the Department;
one representative of the State Department of Education;
one representative of the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene;
one representative of the Department of State Police;
one representative of the Social Services Administration of the Department of Human Resources;
one representative of a private child welfare agency;
one representative of a youth services bureau;
three representatives of the State judiciary;
one representative of the General Assembly recommended by the President of the Senate;
one representative of the General Assembly recommended by the Speaker of the House; and
seven members of the general public.
